[1] Brazil: 2nd in cases, 2nd in deaths
Date: Sat 13 Jun 2020 07:00 IST
Source: Times Now News, AP report [edited]
https://www.timesnownews.com/international/article/coronavirus-brazil-topples-britain-to-become-second-worst-affected-country-in-the-world/605740


The alarming increase in the number of coronavirus-related fatalities in Brazil continued on Friday [12 Jun 2020] as the South American nation recorded around 909 deaths in the last 24 hours alone. Brazil's total death toll now stands at 41 828, and it has surpassed Britain to become the 2nd worst-affected country by COVID-19 in the world after the USA.

According to official reports, the sharp increase in virus-related cases and deaths in Brazil will continue for now while the experts suggest the actual number of coronavirus cases in the country might be 10 or 15 times higher than the existing number. Brazil, the largest country in South America, is not far away from touching one million coronavirus cases, as the number currently stands at 828 810. The only country to hit one million infections is the USA.

It should be noted that Brazil reported its 1st COVID-19 case some 3.5 months ago, and the coronavirus situation is still far from being controlled in the country. Despite the rampant spike in cases and deaths, Brazil administration has reopened activities in major cities like Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo to boost the economy.

Sao Paulo state, with 46 million people, is by far the hardest-hit in Brazil with 10 368 deaths -- about a quarter of the country's total -- and 167 900 infections. Rio de Janeiro has seen 7417 deaths and nearly 78 000 cases of coronavirus so far.

In terms of coronavirus cases, the USA leads the global charts with a staggering number of 2.04 million infections. Brazil comes at 2nd with 828 810 cases, while Russia follows next with 510 761 cases. India stands at the 4th spot with 297 535 cases, while Britain completes the top 5 with 294 402 confirmed cases of coronavirus.

--
