<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Ministry of Health maintains statistics on the "novo coronavirus" (SARS-CoV-2) at https://covid.saude.gov.br/. There are excellent statistics on the geographic breakdown of cases and cumulative population-based rates: In terms of absolute numbers, Sao Paulo state has the highest number of cases followed by the states of Ceara, Para, Pernambuco, Rio de Janeiro, Paraiba, Maranhao, Amapa, Bahia, and Espirito Santo with the 10th highest number of cases. Sao Paulo is the hardest hit state in terms of absolute numbers, and it has a population-based rate of 365.6 per 100 000 population and a population-based mortality rate is 22.6 per 100 000 population. However, the state with the highest population-based rate is Amapa, in the north of the country with a rate of 1854.4 per 100 000 population. Amapa is bordered by French Guiana to its north, the Atlantic Ocean to its east, Para state to its south and west and Suriname to its northwest. The other states with population-based rates higher than 1000 per 100 000 population (i.e.; 1%) are also in the North Region, including Amazonas, Roraima, and Acre. For graphic presentations of the epi curves and mapping, see https://susanalitico.saude.gov.br/#/dashboard/.

A good map of Brazil showing states is available at https://www.mapsofworld.com/brazil/brazil-political-map.html. - Mod.MPP]

