Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:
------------------------------------------
The Americas region reported 55.2% of the global newly reported cases and 69.1% of newly reported fatalities for this 24-hour period. Brazil reported 43.7% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, the USA reported 27.0%, Chile 7.4%, Peru 6.8%, and Mexico 6.5%.

The European region reported 14.5% of the global newly reported cases and 11.5% of newly reported fatalities for this 24-hour period. Russia reported 45.4% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, followed by Sweden 7.4%, the UK 6.4%, Turkey 5.0%, Belarus 3.8%, and Ukraine 3.4%.

The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 14.1% of the global newly reported cases and 7.4% of global newly reported fatalities. Pakistan reported 31.0% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Saudi Arabia 19.3%, Iran 11.6%, Qatar 7.6%, Egypt 7.5%, and Iraq 6.5%.

The African region reported 4.2% of the global newly reported cases and 2.2% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 55.4% of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Nigeria 12.0%, Cote d'Ivoire 3.9%, Gabon 3.0%, Ethiopia 2.9%, Ghana 2.8%, and Central African Republic 2.7%.

The Western Pacific region reported 0.74% of the global newly reported cases and 0.24% of global fatalities. The Philippines reported 57.3% of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Singapore 34.9%, South Korea 3.5%, and Japan 3.2%.

The South East Asia region reported 11.5% of the global newly reported cases and 8.0% of global fatalities. India reported 67.8% of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 21.6%, Indonesia 8.4%, and Nepal 1.9%.

Impression: Europe seems to be stabilizing at a significantly lower rate, although Russia is still reporting 8000+ new cases a day. The Eastern Mediterranean is approximately at parity with the European region with Pakistan reporting 5000+ cases a day. South East Asia is approaching parity with the European and Eastern Mediterranean regions with India reporting 8000-10 000+ cases a day. The Americas region is reporting over 70 000 cases a day with Brazil reporting 25 000-30 000+ cases a day, and the USA seems to have stabilized at 20 000+ a day. In the Africa region, the regional proportion is slowly climbing with South Africa reporting in the 2000-3000+ range daily, and in the Western Pacific region they are maintaining a very low rate compared with the other regions, with Singapore and the Philippines averaging 400+ cases per day (Singapore had been reporting twice as many cases per day for a period of time but has dropped back over the past couple of weeks).

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 12 Jun 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent representation of the epidemic starting in the Western Pacific, transitioning to multiregional activity as the virus travelled. Europe has significantly decreased. The Americas region continues to increase, as does South East Asia, which is approaching parity with the European region in terms of daily newly confirmed cases, and the Eastern Mediterranean, which has surpassed the European region, and the African region is noticeably increasing as well. The Americas region continues to greatly outnumber all other regions for daily reporting. - Mod.MPP]

