[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of reported cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 7 732 485, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The global case count increased by 1.8% in the past 24 hours. The USA, with more than 2.11 million confirmed cases, now represents 27.4% of the global cases of COVID-19, as other countries such as Brazil, Chile, Peru, Mexico, India, and Pakistan are increasing their numbers of cumulative cases significantly. A global total of 428 236 deaths have been reported, an increase of 4392 deaths in the past 24 hours. A reminder that in the absence of well-developed contact tracing activities with testing of asymptomatic and mildly ill contacts, there is major underreporting of numbers of infections with the SARS-CoV-2 virus, possibly 1/10th to 1/20th in order of magnitude. There are also individuals who stay at home throughout their illness, sometimes unfortunately dying at home and are never officially confirmed as infected with the SARS-CoV-2. These data are presented to provide relative indicators of the situations in each of the countries and comparisons between countries and regions of the world.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for cumulative confirmed cases of COVID-19, followed by Brazil, Russia, India, the UK, Spain, Italy, Peru, Germany, and Iran at number 10. China is number 18. This ordering has not changed in the past 24 hours. In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, followed by Brazil, India, Russia, Chile, Peru, Mexico, Saudi Arabia, Bangladesh, and South Africa -- Pakistan did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours, so South Africa joined the top 10 list for number of newly confirmed cases.

The top 20 countries in terms of absolute cumulative cases, which include 7 from the European region, 6 from the Americas region, 4 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 2 from the South-East Asia region, and 1 from the Western Pacific region -- unchanged in the past 96 hours. There are no countries from the Africa region. The top 20 countries with most newly confirmed cases include 8 from the Americas region, 5 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 from the European region, 2 from the South-East Asia region, and 1 from the African region -- none from the Western Pacific region. There was 1 additional country from the European region (Turkey) and 1 fewer country from the Eastern Mediterranean region (Pakistan). This listing very much reflects the "hot spots" in terms of countries with ongoing high transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 virus. - Mod.MPP]
